This is a productive way to look for businesses. Instead of asking, “What service should I sell?” ask:

What loop are people stuck in that keeps recreating the same problem?

A maintenance business gets paid not because something is broken, but because entropy is relentless. The customer is outsourcing a recurring battle against physics, biology, chemistry, or information overload.

Here are some major “decay loops” that already exist—and where new businesses can still emerge.

Loop	Underlying process	Maintenance service
Grass grows	Biology	Landscaping
Trash decomposes	Biology	Trash can cleaning
Dust accumulates	Physics	House cleaning
Gutters clog	Gravity + plants	Gutter cleaning
Roofs grow algae	Biology	Roof washing
HVAC filters clog	Airborne particles	Filter replacement
Cars accumulate wear	Friction	Auto maintenance
Teeth accumulate plaque	Biology	Dentistry
Hair grows	Biology	Barber
Skin accumulates damage	Biology + UV	Dermatology/spa
Software accumulates vulnerabilities	Complexity	Managed IT
Accounts accumulate fraud risk	Human behavior	Auditing

